<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Lubricating Oil Pump, Oil
        Filter, and Cooler - Install
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s210010904">
        <title>Install</title>
        <svcproc id="s210010904.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
            <title>Install Oil Filter and Header</title>
            <para>Oil filter cartridge and oil header can only be installed if engine is off stand.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install water outlet tube in front cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install oil cooler assembly with new square cut O-ring at front header and new O-ring
                    gasket at rear header.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install oil pressure relief valve in crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install filter header and oil cooler assembly on crankcase. Install appropriate bolts
                    and nuts. Tighten nuts on bolts to "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_248.xml" xrefid="t210010903">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010918" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5040.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install water outlet tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Water outlet tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f210010919" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install oil cooler</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolts</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install water inlet tube in crankcase. Install retainer plate for water coolant supply
                    tube and tighten bolt.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid engine damage, do not overtighten filter. A damaged filter may fracture or leak.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid possible engine damage, do not remove adapter and place a long oil filter in place of
                        a short oil filter on severe service applications.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>On some severe service applications a short oil filter and filter adapter have been
                        installed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">(For short oil filter applications) Insure filter adapter is in place and sealed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate filter gasket on new oil filter with clean engine oil. Install new oil filter
                    on filter header.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten filter one full turn after gasket contacts filter header.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010920" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install oil filter</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prime the lubricating system. See "Prime Lubricating System" in this section.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
